<TITLE> Road accident kills 2 in Sirajganj </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sirajganj, June 4 (bdnews24.com)  Two people died and 15 others were injured after a bus and a truck collided at Bhuiyangati area on Bogra-Nagarbari highway under Raiganj upazila early Wednesday. Hatikumrul highway police chief Tozammel Hossain said, the accident occurred at around 4:00 am while a Dhaka bound bus of Keya Paribahan coming from Syedpur collided head-on with a Mymensingh bound truck laden with fish coming from Raiganj, veered off the highway and fell into a roadside ditch. Nayan, 32, helper of the bus and Shukur Ali of Moulavi Bazar, a passenger died on the spot. The injured were admitted to Raiganj upazila health complex and other local clinics. bdnews24.co
